contentrichtext.text: {{unreferenced|date=April 2009}} '''Voldemar Oinonen''' (1891-1963) was a [[Finnish Defence Forces|Finnish military]] commander. ==Ranks== * 1939-1940 Assistant Chief General Staff * 1940 [[General Officer Commanding]] 23rd Division * 1940 General Officer Commanding 11th Separate Division * 1940-1941 Acting General Officer Commanding [[Finnish III Corps (Winter War)|III Corps]] * 1941-1942 General Officer Commanding Group Oinonen * 1942-1944 [[Chief of Staff]] of the Home Troops * 1944 Acting [[Commander-in-Chief|Commander in Chief]] of the Home Troops {{Persondata <!-- Metadata: see [[Wikipedia:Persondata]]. --> | NAME = Oinonen, Voldemar | ALTERNATIVE NAMES = | SHORT DESCRIPTION = | DATE OF BIRTH = 1891 | PLACE OF BIRTH = | DATE OF DEATH = 1963 | PLACE OF DEATH = }} {{DEFAULTSORT:Oinonen, Voldemar}} [[Category:1891 births]] [[Category:1963 deaths]] [[Category:Finnish military personnel]]
